caption.text:
RESULTS!! ⤵️

• Likes — 28,298
• Saves — 1,031
• Shares — 1,004* (note: this does NOT include Shares to me!)
• Comments — 637
• Avg. Watch Time — 0:12

Shares to me — 30,000 (estimate)

Based off this info, we can assume that Shares boost views because the algorithm pushes content that get’s a lot of Shares,
NOT just because Shared posts get viewed by the recipients of the post.

So HOW do you get MORE SHARES?

Create Share-worthy posts! ⤵️
1️⃣ Motivational — content that inspires others.

2️⃣ Call to arms — content that asks for help, involves the community, or spreads awareness. Think of the ALC Ice Bucket Challenge!

3️⃣ Relatable — the type of post that makes you say “that is so me.” This is often memes and funny clips!

4️⃣ Controversial — Unpopular opinions and “contrary to popular belief” posts are highly share-worthy! People LOVE it when someone finally speaks up & says what they’ve been thinking.

5️⃣ News/Pop Culture — Breaking News, pop culture, and timely updates are super shareworthy.

JUST DON’T FORGET:
Your Share-worthy posts NEED to be related to your niche!!

⭐️ Start making shareworthy content and you will grow!!!

P.S. if you’ve read this far, I hope you consider sharing this post so that more creators and business owners can learn about creating share-worthy posts!! 🥰

caption.text:
TIP FOR POSTING MORE (without burnout) ⬇️

But wait, before you scroll, make sure you "Like" this Reel (:

1. UPCYCLE!!

You should be REPOSTing, RECYCLING, and REMIXING your posts every 90 days!

75% of my posts are upcycled posts from the past - THAT is how I'm able to post so much!

2. FECK PERFUCTION!!

Stop trying to make perfect posts. GOOD ENOUGH IS GOOD ENOUGH!

3. OUTSOURCE!!

Whether its the use of Ai or real humans, get as much help as you can!

4. SCHEDULE!!

Trying to make a new post every day WILL LEAD TO BURNOUT!

Instead, batch, schedule, and plan in advance!!

It'll give you the freedom to create when you WANT TO vs. feeling like you HAVE TO!

caption.text:
If you want to grow on instagram, STOP stressing out over quality. 

Now I need to make this clear: Quality matters! It absolutely does.

But my issue is: focusing on quality often leads to perfectionism, over-comparison, and burnout.

Quantity, on the other hand, CREATES quality.

Quantity is practice!!

Also, from an algorithm perspective, THE MORE YOU POST, THE MORE YOUR GROW! 

So yes, quality matters, but quantity is how you get there.
